definitions.definition: A sole owner of an unincorporated business , also called a sole proprietor .
One of the owners of an unincorporated business, a partner .
One or more persons to whom a colonial territory is assigned, like a fief , including its administration.
examples: From 10 September 1621 till 12 June 1632, Sir William Alexander, styled Earl of Stirling and Viscount of Canada, was proprietor of the Scottish colony Nova Scotia.
